HEADWORD: Unspeak
<hw>Un*speak"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>speak</ets>.]</ety> <def>To retract, as what has
been spoken; to recant; to unsay.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

